BBNaija’s ex-housemate, Tuoyo has survived an auto-crash in Lagos.  The reality TV show star shared a video of his badly damaged vehicle after the accident, which occurred on Ozumba Mbadiwe Road, Victoria Island, Lagos. “I just had a terrible accident but I am grateful to God that I survived as well as all those in the vehicle. I can’t believe this but thank God,” he said. He shared a post on his Instagram page with the caption: “Thank God for life and everyone that was with me. Nothing shall take our life this year in Jesus name.” Tuoyo, a model and actor, became popular after he participated in the BBNaija lockdown edition, which was won by Laycon. Popular fashion designer and younger brother of Nigerian Comedian AY, Yomi Casual, is recuperating in a Lagos hospital after he survived a ghastly motor accident on Sunday. Yomi Casual, who shared a picture of his wrecked car and another picture of him lying on a hospital bed on his Instagram… In "Entertainment" After being evicted from the house, BBNaija housemate, Tuoyo has revealed that Mercy is his kind of girl.  Tuoyo and Mercy dancing First male housemate to be evicted from the BBNaija season four house, Tuoyo who has been on tours since his eviction from the show last Sunday, July 21,  was… In "Entertainment" Tuoyo Ideh, an ex-Big Brother Naija season 4 housemate has come clean on his claim of being a stripper while on the reality show. In an Instagram post he shared, the reality show star admitted that he lied and has been stuck with the lie for over a year. He… In "News"